data.value:
How to use: 1) On first run, click "Install Requirements" in the top right" 2) Copy/paste a git url from github or other hosting site into Git URL 3) Put a project name in "Clone to" 4) Click 5) If the project docs say it needs "pip libraries" or similar, put that filename into the box labeled "Pip" 5b) Click "Install from file" 6) Look in the project page for the line similar to: " python <filename here>.py " 6b) Enter this in the box labeled "Main File" 7) Click run project
------
To set app to project you've already cloned and pip installed, use the box in the bottom right, before entering "main file" value.
